doc.previous: In the arts, Liverpool was home to the first lending library, athenaeum society, arts centre[52] and public art conservation centre.[53] Liverpool is also home to the UK's oldest surviving classical orchestra, the Royal Liverpool Philharmonic Orchestra,[54] as well as the oldest surviving repertory theatre, the Liverpool Playhouse.[55]
doc.after: In 1864, Peter Ellis built the world's first iron-framed, curtain-walled office building, Oriel Chambers, the prototype of the skyscraper. The UK's first purpose-built department store was Compton House, completed in 1867 for the retailer J.R. Jeffrey;[56] it was the largest store in the world at the time.[57]
